concept_explanation.protobuf:
**Protocol Buffers — binary serialization:**

```protobuf
// payment.proto
syntax = "proto3";

package com.razorpay.payment;
option java_package = "com.razorpay.payment.grpc";
option java_outer_classname = "PaymentProto";

// Message: like a Java record
message PaymentRequest {
  string merchant_id = 1;   // field number (unique, immutable)
  int64 amount_paise = 2;
  string gateway = 3;
  PaymentType type = 4;
}

// Enum:
enum PaymentType {
  PAYMENT_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED = 0;  // proto3: always a 0 default
  CREDIT_CARD = 1;
  UPI = 2;
  NETBANKING = 3;
}

// Nested message:
message PaymentResponse {
  string payment_id = 1;
  PaymentStatus status = 2;
  string error_message = 3;     // empty if success

  message Metadata {
    string gateway_ref = 1;
    int64 processed_at = 2;     // Unix timestamp
  }
  Metadata metadata = 4;
}

// Service definition:
service PaymentService {
  rpc CreatePayment (PaymentRequest) returns (PaymentResponse);
  rpc GetPaymentStatus (PaymentStatusRequest) returns (PaymentResponse);
}
```

concept_explanation.grpc_types:
**4 gRPC call types:**

```protobuf
service TradeService {
  // 1. Unary: one request → one response (like REST)
  rpc PlaceOrder (OrderRequest) returns (OrderResponse);

  // 2. Server streaming: one request → multiple responses
  rpc WatchPrices (WatchRequest) returns (stream PriceUpdate);

  // 3. Client streaming: multiple requests → one response
  rpc UploadTrades (stream TradeRecord) returns (UploadSummary);

  // 4. Bidirectional streaming: multiple ↔ multiple
  rpc OrderBook (stream OrderUpdate) returns (stream BookSnapshot);
}
```

